commit.message:
configure: add go version to summary

When displaying configure summary, include the go version.

Add math expansion variables.

  This adds new expansion variables $[math.+.<x>,<y>],
  $[math.-.<x>,<y>], $[math.*.<x>,<y>], $[math./.<x>,<y>],
  $[math.%.<x>,<y>], and $[math.^.<x>,<y>], which can be
  used to do basic integer mathematics on the integers <x> and <y>.
  The comma in <x>,<y> allows for using floats in the future.

  This also updates the default-config to use these expansion
  variables instead of a shell to do the mathematics in its size
  computation.

Use AX_COMPARE_VERSION macro for golang version checks

The previous approach was fragile, required manual updates,
and results in unexpected outcomes when the user has updated
golang.

Reported-by: Denny Rivetti <denny.rivetti.me@gmail.com>

Don't use a declaration state in for loops

This breaks builds with older gcc ex: EL7 gcc 4.8.5

Make desktop buttons bigger in RightPanel

  Increase the size of the desktop buttons in the RightPanel from
  25x20 to 25x25. This makes them square, and better able to deal
  with increasing the dpi of the font.
TODO.md: mark some actions as completed

INSTALL.md: mention --enable-htmldoc

Mention the --enable-htmldoc flag to ./configure to generate HTML pages.

DEVELOPERS.md: master -> main

The default branch has been "main" for a while, but the documentation
wasn't updated to reflect this.
set next version
[AUTO]: release 1.1.0

FvwmPager: free vars on ExitPager

When the FvwmPager is closed/killed, ensure we free some of the
variables which had been malloc()d.

Don't let windows have zero size.

  Allowing the height or width of a window to become zero can
  causes them to misbehave (noticed this when switching between
  monitors). Use MinSize instead of zero for windows in this case.

Add preferred monitor logic to FvwmPager.

  First, this fixes an issue if monitor_to_track is set and that monitor
  is disconnected, then fvwm pager stops tracking anything. Instead,
  if monitor_to_track is disconnected, monitor_to_track will switch
  to the current monitor instead. If that monitor is enabled again,
  fvwm will resume tracking it.

Make FQueryPointer a void function.

  There should be no reason this function should ever return false,
  now that fvwm will always occupy all screens. Remove the extra logic
  checking around this function and make it a void function.

Remove single screen support, -s.

  Fvwm no longer needs to run separate instances on each screen
  to manage screens independently. With RandR support and
  DesktopConfiguration per-monitor, each screen can be managed
  independently, with the advantage that all windows are managed by
  a single instance of fvwm, so windows can be moved between screens
  to. This removes single screen support from fvwm.

virtual: silence compiler warning

Even though "m" will be set, still explicitly set it to NULL upon
initialisation, so that GCC is kept happy.

Remove use of allow_null bool in fpmonitor_from_xy

  fpmonitor_from_xy(x, y), will now return NULL if no monitor is found
  (and a single monitor is not being tracked, and global mode isn't used).

FvwmPager: remove redundant section

This was never doing anything for "Monitor", as this was being handled
by looking at the module resource lines, instead.

FvwmPager: CalcGeom: initial rectangle off screen

If CalcGeom isn't sent a valid monitor or is sent a monitor
different than the one being tracked, the default rectangle
is returned. Place this default rectangle off the screen like
is done with other windows.

FvwmPager: Shorten fallback labels

The fallback labels are for small buttons, make these smaller.

This makes the fallback label for a monitor its fvwm pager's
monitor number, and the fall back label for a desk "D%d", which
is the desk number prepended with "D" to distinguish desk labels
from monitor labels.

FvwmPager: CalGeom: don't segfault on NULL

When calculating the rectangle we want to use, check fp is NULL
otherwise FvwmPager would crash trying to dereference a NULL
value.

FvwmPager: MonitorLabels only show the monitor being tracked.

  If *FvwmPager: Monitor is set to a valid monitor, the MonitorLabels
  will now only show the single monitor being tracked.

FvwmPager: right click scroll fixes.

  When using DesktopConfiguration share, make sure the correct monitor
  is identified when scrolling on a desk that a monitor is currently
  viewing.  When scrolling on the icon view, only scroll a monitor
  in the clicked area if that monitor is currently viewing the same
  desk as the pager (in other words don't scroll a monitor on a
  different desk).

FvwmPager: show MonitorLabels independent of DeskLabels

This adds two new options DeskLabels and NoDeskLabels to FvwmPager to
allow turning on/off the desk labels. In addition this simplifies the
logic for testing if labels are shown and allows one to configure
showing only desk labels, only monitor labels, no labels, or both desk
and monitor labels.

FvwmPager: add MonitorLabels and 'shared' support

FvwmPager can now better deal with DesktopConfiguration shared.
It now understand is_tracking_shared and will show the correct
location of windows and monitors in this mode. In addition clicks
to the pager will be ignored, unless clicking in a desk occupied
by a monitor. In that case the current monitor occupying the desk
will move to the page clicked.

In order to be able to move through desks and pages in shared
mode a new feature MonitorLabels was added. This will print a row
of current monitors under the desk labels. Each monitor label
acts as a button and will move the monitor to the desktop the
button was clicked in. This works in any mode, but when in shared
mode this is the only way to move monitors between desktops
reliably.

DesktopConfiguration: broadcast is_tracking_shared

When sending the monitor list to modules, also send down the value of
is_tracking_shared, so that FvwmPager can track this.

FvwmPager: disable expose bound event checks

This optimization might not be needed and with the plan to add
monitor labels the logic is a bit to much for any possible gain.

Removing the code for now.

FvwmPager: fix initial size of desk windows

The desk title window and window initial position/size should not be
based off the view port size, instead use the desk and label size.

FvwmPager: Allow label clicks when Monitor set

When FvwmPager is configured to track a specific monitor, allow
the desk label to switch desks.
FvwmPager man page face lift.
